                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1076">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Austria)/5–1045:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Alexander C. Kirk</persName>,
                        Political Adviser, Allied Force Headquarters, to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caserta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-10T20:00:00+02:00"
                            >May 10, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 10—2:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2066. My 1336 of April 4 midnight. We have learned that Tito<note n="67"
                        xml:id="d1076fn67">Marshal Josip Broz Tito, Yugoslav Premier and Minister of
                        National Defense.</note> has informed British representatives in Belgrade
                    that he has received a favorable reply from Soviet Government to his request
                    that section of Austrian territory be occupied by his forces and that up to
                    present <pb facs="1330" n="1318" xml:id="pg_1318"/> time no reply has been
                    forthcoming from British and American Governments. Statement was also made by
                    Tito that he intended to hold any Austrian territory which his troops might
                    seize.</p>
                <p>Reports reaching AFHQ<note n="68" xml:id="d1076fn68">Allied Force
                        Headquarters.</note> indicate that Tito is insisting on Yugoslav Government
                    for Carinthia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
